sections.comments: Restricted to BMUS, BA (MUSC) or MIN (MUSC) in year 3 or higher. Topic:  Medieval Music. Music and musical culture of the Middle Ages in Western Europe, from the emergence of written notation in the ninth century to the end of the fourteenth century.2020W Format:  Every week, students study online course materials on their own time (asynchronously).Every week they must attend a 40-minute online tutorial, chosen freely from four sessions that will be held between 9:30 and 11 am on Monday and Wednesdays.

description: Sacred and secular music, vocal and instrumental.
